The students are getting familiar with presenting scientific text according to the rules of Estonian grammar. They compile a review of BSc thesis written before by some other person. With the help of his/her supervisor, every student compiles a plan and one chapter of his/her own BSc thesis, and presents them at the seminar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to develop the oral and written communicative skills of students in Estonian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student is expected to: 1.	Be able to compile a grammatically correct written text for the chosen field of research;  2.	Be able to compile an exhaustive referative summary of literature considering a certain scientific problem; 3.	Within the defined limits, be able to present in Estonian a summary of a certain scientific problem.
